                <div>Submit Project can remain, but it should live inside the founder area rather than as a standalone top-level navigation action.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="screen-card">
          <div class="screen-card-header" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <div class="screen-card-left">
              <div class="screen-icon" style="background: rgba(62,207,142,0.12);">⚡</div>
              <div>
                <h3>Dashboard (New Page)</h3>
                <div class="screen-sub">Authenticated landing and operating center</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
              <span class="priority-badge p-new">New</span>
              <span class="chevron">▾</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="screen-card-body">
            <div class="change-list">
              <div class="change-item">
                <div class="change-icon ci-add">+</div>
                <div><strong style="color: var(--text);">Access overview module</strong> showing BLOCK staked, lock duration, multiplier, points, rank, and access status.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="change-item">
                <div class="change-icon ci-add">+</div>
                <div><strong style="color: var(--text);">Open pools module</strong> for currently active opportunities, prioritized by urgency or close date.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="change-item">
                <div class="change-icon ci-add">+</div>
                <div><strong style="color: var(--text);">Wallet readiness module</strong> showing connected chains, missing wallets, and whether the user is ready for EVM and Solana participation.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="change-item">
                <div class="change-icon ci-add">+</div>
                <div><strong style="color: var(--text);">Recent activity feed</strong> for investments, claims, staking changes, and pool status updates.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Execution</div>
      <h2>Implementation Priority</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Ordered by structural impact. Phase 1 fixes broken logic. Phase 2 adds missing product layers. Phase 3 is polish.</p>

      <div class="priority-timeline">
        <div class="priority-item">
          <div class="priority-phase">Phase 1 — Fix Core Logic</div>
          <h4>Remove dual staking references</h4>
          <p>Update homepage, explanatory content, and supporting stats to reflect single staking and points-based access.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item">
          <h4>Remove tier system from profile</h4>
          <p>Replace old tier badges with an access overview based on lock duration, multiplier, points, and rank.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item">
          <h4>Implement confirmed pool state system</h4>
          <p>Map cards and detail views to scheduled, phase 1, phase 2, sold out, failed, and claim-ready behavior.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item">
          <h4>Fix disabled CTA patterns</h4>
          <p>Every blocked action needs a reason and a next step. No silent dead ends.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item upcoming">
          <div class="priority-phase">Phase 2 — Add Missing Product Layers</div>
          <h4>Build dashboard page</h4>
          <p>Create the authenticated operating center with access overview, open pools, wallet readiness, and recent activity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item upcoming">
          <h4>Restructure navigation</h4>
          <p>Merge Deals and Launch Pools into Pools, move Submit Project into founder area, and clarify support vs app navigation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item upcoming">
          <h4>Add Solana support layer</h4>
          <p>Introduce chain tags, wallet readiness logic, and sold-out routing that adapts to Solana-specific participation flows.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item upcoming">
          <h4>Expand founder lifecycle</h4>
          <p>Grow the founder area into a full lifecycle system with filters, badges, and visibility across all project states.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item upcoming">
          <div class="priority-phase">Phase 3 — Polish</div>
          <h4>Token Claims contextual reasons</h4>
          <p>Replace generic not ready text with contextual TGE, unlock, or next claim timing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="priority-item upcoming">
          <h4>Refine post-pool routing</h4>
          <p>Improve sold-out, failed, and claim-ready states with chain-aware messaging and smoother detail handoff.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Decisions Needed</div>
      <h2>Open Questions</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">These need stakeholder input before the design system can fully lock.</p>

      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-num">Q1</div>
        <h4>What is the final homepage framing for staking now that dual staking is removed?</h4>
        <p>Should staking be presented as single staking, points-based access, staking rewards, or a broader access system?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-num">Q2</div>
        <h4>What is the exact logic connecting stake amount, lock duration, multiplier, points, and leaderboard rank?</h4>
        <p>The access overview module should only expose relationships that are actually confirmed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-num">Q3</div>
        <h4>If overflow becomes part of the allocation model, how should it be handled visually and operationally?</h4>
        <p>Possible directions include pro-rata reduction, waitlist logic, lottery, or another allocation mechanism, but this is not yet a confirmed core state.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-num">Q4</div>
        <h4>Can we confirm failed pools default to automatic refund back to the participation wallet?</h4>
        <p>If manual claim exists, it should be treated as an exception, not the primary flow.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-num">Q5</div>
        <h4>Should dashboard replace homepage for authenticated users, or remain a separate destination?</h4>
        <p>This changes the default landing experience after login.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-num">Q6</div>
        <h4>How should the main wallet vs optional wallet system be surfaced in the UI?</h4>
        <p>The product needs to explain clearly that the main wallet is the staking reference wallet, while optional wallets are used for chain-specific participation, including Solana.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="page-footer">
      <p>Blockstreet Launchpad Redesign Direction — March 2026 — Internal Document</p>
    </div>

  </div>

</body>
</html>
